-123.82208A348.16 348.16 0 1 1 491.52 155.648z m0 622.592a274.432 274.432 0 1 0 0-548.864 274.432 274.432 0 0 0 0 548.864z" fill="currentColor"></path></svg> <span data-v-bc9c95fe="" class="toolcall-title-name-text">Search images</span></div> <span data-v-bc9c95fe="" class="toolcall-title-container-content"><span data-v-bc9c95fe="" class="toolcall-title-container-text">AISC logo official ASTM International logo official AWS D1.1 welding code logo</span> </span> <div data-v-bc9c95fe="" class="toolcall-title-container-extra"><span data-v-9606ddcc="" need-upgrade="false">6 results</span> <svg data-v-bc9c95fe="" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" role="img" class="iconify toolcall-title-container-extra-arrow" width="1em" height="1em" viewBox="0 0 1024 1024" name="Right_b"><path d="M681.00096 549.23264a36.864 36.864 0 0 0-0.08192-52.0192L395.22304 211.47648a36.864 36.864 0 1 0-52.14208 52.10112l259.6864 259.72736-259.76832 261.69344a36.864 36.864 0 0 0 52.30592 51.93728l285.696-287.744z" fill="currentColor"></path></svg></div></div> <!----></div></div></div></div> <!----><!----> <div data-v-3b9ae98b="" data-v-763ce8f9="" class="markdown-container"><div data-v-3b9ae98b="" class="markdown"></div></div><div data-v-763ce8f9="" data-v-2788030a=""><div data-v-9445e104="" data-v-5c7bcb73="" data-v-6f8c130e=""><div data-v-9445e104="" class="resize-container enable-grow-animation" style="height: 14623px;"><div data-v-9445e104="" class="slot-container"><div data-v-5c7bcb73="" class="sandbox-wrapper" style="height: 14623px;"><div data-v-512573ed="" data-v-5c7bcb73="" class="widget-sandbox"><iframe data-v-512573ed="" class="widget-sandbox__frame" src="./Welded Joint Types &amp; Prep - Kimi_files/saved_resource.html" sandbox="allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-forms" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" title="Kimi Widget Sandbox"></iframe></div></div> <!----></div></div> <!----></div></div><!----> <div data-v-3b9ae98b="" data-v-763ce8f9="" class="markdown-container"><div data-v-3b9ae98b="" class="markdown"><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">Your professional engineering presentation is ready above! Here's what's included:</div><div class="paragraph" dir="auto"><strong>8 Interactive Slides:</strong></div><ol start="1"><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto"><strong>Title Slide</strong> — With AISC, ASTM, and AWS logos; presenter details placeholder</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto"><strong>Introduction &amp; Standards</strong> — Welding definition + AISC / ASTM / AWS D1.1 breakdown with workflow</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto"><strong>Types of Welded Joints</strong> — All 5 joints (Butt, Lap, Tee, Corner, Edge) with visual cards and comparison table</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto"><strong>Joint Preparation</strong> — Pre-weld requirements, groove diagrams, and AWS D1.1 tolerance table</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto"><strong>Groove Types &amp; Comparison</strong> — Full selection guide (9 groove types) + comprehensive joint comparison matrix</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto"><strong class="">Applications</strong> — 10 industry sectors with icons + structural insights for buildings, bridges, and pressure vessels</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto"><strong>AISC &amp; ASTM Requirements</strong> — Design requirements, inspection protocols, seismic provisions, material grades table, and the AISC→ASTM→AWS relationship flow</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto"><strong>Conclusion &amp; References</strong> — Key takeaways, primary standards, textbooks, and Q&amp;A closing</div></li></ol><div class="paragraph" dir="auto"><strong>Design Features:</strong></div><ul start="1"><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">Blue, gray, and white professional engineering palette</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">Sticky navigation dots for quick slide jumping</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">Speaker notes on every slide</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">Responsive tables and comparison cards</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">Real engineering diagrams and standard logos</div></li><li><div class="paragraph" dir="auto">Hover animations and smooth scroll transitions</div></li></ul><div class="paragraph" dir="auto"><strong>To use for your seminar:</strong> Scroll through the slides above, or click the navigation dots to jump between slides. Replace <code data-v-8d822fd1="" data-v-3b9ae98b="" class="segment-code-inline">[Your Name]</code>, <code data-v-8d822fd1="" data-v-3b9ae98b="" class="segment-code-inline">[Your College/University]</code>, and <code data-v-8d822fd1="" data-v-3b9ae98b="" class="segment-code-inline">[your.email@university.edu]</code> with your actual details before presenting.</div></div></div> <!----> <!----> <!----></div>  <!----> <!----> <!----> <!---->   <!----> <div data-v-6f8c130e="" class="okc-cards-container"><!----> <!----> <!----> <!----> <!----></div> <!----> <!----> <!----> <div data-v-b1bd13bb="" data-v-2788030a="" class="segment-assistant-actions"><div data-v-b1bd13bb="" class="segment-assistant-actions-content"> <div data-v-4c27bfac="" data-v-b1bd13bb="" class="assistant-page"><div data-v-1005b780="" data-v-4c27bfac="" class="icon-button assistant-page-item" style="width: 28px; height: 28px;"><svg data-v-1005b780="" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" role="img" class="iconify" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 1024 1024" name="Left_b"><path d="M342.99904 549.23264a36.864 36.864 0 0 1 0.08192-52.0192l285.696-285.696a36.864 36.864 0 1 1 52.14208 52.10112l-259.6864 259.72736 259.76832 261.69344a36.864 36.864 0 0 1-52.30592 51.93728L342.99904 549.2736z" fill="currentColor"></path></svg> <!----></div> <span data-v-4c27bfac="" class="assistant-page-info">2/2</span> <div data-v-1005b780="" data-v-4c27bfac="" class="icon-button assistant-page-item disabled" style="width: 28px; hei